<br>
Most of the mobs in there have really silly names, like Tal mentioned Pansies. The whole zone is designed around a god who is a practical joker. <br>
<br>
Most of the mobs wont go KoS on you but there are a few who will. Most of the ones that do you really dont want to be near heh. <br>
<br>
The armor is very decent stuff when you can get it, but as Tal said it is more useful mostly as trinkets. PoM is also currently incomplete and I dont think there is any armor for tanks. Most of valoran's wizards are wearing the PoM robe (blue with purple trim) so if you can find one of them you can see it yourself.<br>
<br>
The port in room is a large square chamber with for mobs in the corners named One Two Three and Four. There's a raised dias in the centre and a Chest spawns on it. On the walls are pictures of Bristlebane (I believe thats the right god) he looks like a smiling halfling with black hair. There are hidden stairways everywhere, the fake doors (when you open them) cast Fear on you as a joke. There are also hidden floors everywhere that drop you into a maze of tunnels that are patrolled by non KOS rats (might have changed)<br>
<br>
The zone itself is a castle, full with moat and everything. The trees in the courtyard have pink and orange leaves and the perimiter of the zone is a very tall phazed blue wall. The port in is 4 hanging blue translucent crystal that are enormous. <br>
<br>
